<text>This is a list of members of the [[International Olympic Committee]]. According to the Olympic Charter, the members of the IOC &quot;represent and promote the interests of the IOC and of the Olympic Movement in their countries and in the organisations of the Olympic Movement in which they serve&quot;. Currently, there are 109 members and 39 honorary members.

==Current members==
The chairperson of an international organization, who represents an Olympic sport (e.g. the chairman of World Athletics), is represented in the IOC &quot;ex officio&quot; (i.e., because of that position).
* Athletes&#x27; Commission members are elected for eight-year terms.

==Honorary Members==
Most honorary members are former members who, after finishing their terms of office, are made honorary members.

